This program will enable your Raspberry Pi to read the values from a gyroscope, accelerometer & magnetometer and convert them to usable angles and heading.
It also includes tilt compensation for compass heading. Utilises both the Complementary and Kalman filters.
Go here for more information;

http://ozzmaker.com/


This script supports the LS6MDSL (gyro and accelerometer) and MMC5983 (compass) which is included in the OzzMaker LTE-M IMU board


Run using;
python berryIMU.py					
python berryIMU-simple.py           #Simple version using only complementary filter 
python calibrateBerryIMU.py			#Used to calibrate compass
